#Text=Star Wars character Jabba the Hutt , a puppet in the 1983 film Return of the Jedi , was re-created by the 501st Legion as an animatronic .
#Text=The 501st is a fan group that dresses like the series villains for charitable events , particularly those raising funds for the Make-A-Wish Foundation .
#Text=The new addition to their annual display commanded long lineups throughout the day , from con-goers looking to donate in exchange for a photo-op with the massive , slug-like alien .
#Text=Jabba the Hutt animatronic .
#Text=Image : Nicholas Moreau .
#Text=Ahsoka , operating the camera at the 501st 's booth .
#Text=Image : Nicholas Moreau .
#Text=Jawas and Tusken Raiders at a Vikings TV show photo op .

#Text=Comic Corps of Canada fundraising .
#Text=Image : Nicholas Moreau .

#Text=As with most major conventions , cosplayers were numerous , ranging from simple outfits that would n't raise an eyebrow if worn from day-to-day , to elaborately-created costumes and giant props .

#Text=Outfits recognized by Wikinews ' reporter ranged from classic characters like the 1960s version of Batgirl and Oswald the Lucky Rabbit , a character created by Walt Disney in 1927 , before Mickey , to 2010s characters from creative works like Undertale , Disney Descendants , League of Legends , and Adventure Time .
#Text=Few characters are too obscure , if they appeal to a fan : the female avatar of “ hivemind ” character Unity , from a single episode of Rick and Morty , was spotted .

#Text=One woman “ biting ” another woman 's arm would be cause for concern most places , but at a pop culture convention , it simply means that “ Lilo ” is re-enacting a scene with “ Mertle ” , as seen in the film Lilo and Stitch .

#Text=Cheryl , right , talked with Wikinews .
#Text=Image : Nicholas Moreau .

#Text=Wikinews talked with Cheryl , the co-host of the weekly video series " Our Didnee Side " , who was dressed as Gadget Hackwrench , a mouse from the 1990s television series Chip ' n Dale : Rescue Rangers .
#Text=Speaking for both of the hosts , she said their passion for Disney has “ exploded ” since starting the YouTube channel , and that they are both “ creators .
#Text=We ca n't seem to go a day without making something .
#Text=We love doing Disney cosplay because it is like a beacon for other people in the fandom to come find us in a sea of other characters . ”
#Text=Conventions like Fan Expo Canada become “ a great opportunity to meet like-minded Disney fans , and to possibly escape for the weekend from our ' boring human ' lives . ”
